čBehind this bench stood the magnificent neo-gothic red brick
building of St Paul's School from 1884 to 1968.
Celebrated Architect: Alfred Waterhouse
Boys were evacuated in WW2 and it became the HQ for 21st Army Group
commanded by former pupil General Montgomery.
The final decision to invade Normandy was taken here on 15th May 1944,
about which President Eisenhower wrote:
"During the whole of the war I attended no other
conference so packed with rank as this one."
King George VI, Prime Minister Winston Churchill, Generals Montgomery
and Eisenhower were amongst 146 present in the Lecture Theatre.
Bench presented by the Old Pauline Trust Ltd
to commemorate the 75th Anniversary of D-Day on 6th June 2019."ų
ėLeighton-Davies
John 1883-1983 and Amelia, nee Theaker 1887-1982
John 1918-2013 and Jean, nee Hills 1920-1982
Remembered, especially here, by their family

How sweet the moonlight sleeps upon this bank!
Here will we sit, and let the sound of music
Creep in our ears: soft stiliness and the night
Become the touches of sweet harmony"ž
šWALTER LEARY
17th Feb.1920 - 23rd Dec.1994
COUNCILLOR ST.KATHERINE'S WARD 1964-1985
Kingdoms may come, Kingdoms may go
Whatever the end may be
But Old Father Thames keeps rolling along
Down to the mighty sea"█
